The '''black-hooded sierra finch''' ('''''Phrygilus atriceps''''') is a species of [[bird]] in the family [[Thraupidae]].

It is found in [[Argentina]], [[Bolivia]], [[Chile]], and [[Peru]]. Its natural [[habitat]]s are subtropical or tropical moist [[montane forest]]s and subtropical or tropical high-altitude [[shrubland]].[[File:Cometocino del Norte, Quebrada Guatín, 07feb13 007.jpg|thumb|Black hooded sierra finch, near San Pedro de Atacama, Chile|left]]

